Apriori

- people who bought/see something also bought/see something else
- association rule
- identify strong rules

Algo has 3 parts:
  1. Support
  2. Confidence
  3. lift

Movie recommend:  
Find support: setup minimum support and confidence
support(M) = (# of user watchlists containing a movie)/(# of user watchlists)

Find confidence: 
confidence(M1 -> M2) = (# of user watchlists containing M1 and M2)/(# of user watchlists containing M1)

lift(M1 -> M2) = confidence(M1->M2)/support(M1->M2)

Apriori:
1. Set minimum support & confidence
2. Take all subsets in transactions having higher support than minimum support
3. Take all the rules of these subsets having higher confidence than minimum confidence
4. sort the rules by decreasing lift

- Recommender systems use this algo with other algos and modifications



